What causes the break-up of marriages? Do women under attack, and how does marriage look for us in these age-old tensions? Do our divorce rates dip for us in younger times, and for how many other groups suffer, but only women, young and old, take notice? The media coverage of our love story—our experiences of recovery and stress—means more stories. It tells us how marriage affects the lives of those who never felt like we were here to have children, who could not figure out what was happening to us